title: Matlock | New Season Official Trailer | CBS
description:
Emmy and Academy Award winner Kathy Bates stars as Matty Matlock, a brilliant attorney who rejoins the work force at a prestigious law firm where she uses clever tactics to win cases while hiding a hidden agenda. Matty works for Olympia (Skye P. Marshall), a new partner, whose ex-husband Julian (Jason Ritter) is the son of the head of the firm. She works alongside the firmâ€™s younger associates, Billy (David Del Rio) and Sarah (Leah Lewis).

title: Kathy Bates on Losing 100 Lbs., â€˜Matlockâ€™ and Retirement Rumors | PEOPLE
description:
Kathy Bates talks to PEOPLE about losing 100 pounds, her new role on 'Matlock' and when she plans to retire from acting. She discusses her 6-year health journey and clears the air about Ozempic rumors: "I lost about 80 pounds [without medication], and the last 15 or 20 is always the hardest, so when Ozempic came out, I thought 'OK' and I went to my doctor."

http://itunes.apple.com/us/album/2707/id411777685

If you didn't get this you're on my shitlist

Tell your friends about them yo but this the "shush"

I'm the new Jesse Jacks', operation PUSH
 
(hook)
Brand new Nikes on, brand new hat
Fresh out your bitch with a brand new rap
Knock Knock motherfucker, guess who's back?
With some shit for your ass, where the fuck y'all at?

And mr. show-promoter better have my gwap

That's right motherfucker guess who's back?
With some shit for your ass, where the fuck y'all at?
 
(verse 3)
Everybody talking' 'bout your boy ain't right
'Cause I cross out tags in the broad daylight
I built my name out of bricks not hype

My first two shits', had hits accidentally

Mixtape, sick straight through to the endin' G
2707, crime of the century

Swim with the big fish, you bound to drizz-own
Middle finger up, never turn my shit down
I'll get down 'til I'm up in a cage
Got paid, no one's seen me in a couple of days
Puffin' haze, cuffin' strays, son I'm stuck in my ways
Ain't dumb in brains, I'm just too fuckin' stubborn to change

title: "Matlock" star Kathy Bates
description:
Academy Award-winning actress Kathy Bates sits down with Turner Classic Movies host Ben Mankiewicz to talk about her new TV show "Matlock," which explores the "invisibility" of women of a certain age. She also discusses some of her most memorable stage and screen roles, including her performance as a violent psychopath in the Stephen King thriller "Misery," and the message she shared with her late mother the night she won the Oscar.

title: Classic TV Theme: Matlock (Full Stereo)
description: It's the stereotypical 'old people's show' but one of the most erudite film commentators I've heard was a major Matlock fan. He loved to watch how Matlock would ensnare the guilty party in his trap. Viewers did too, for nine seasons, with all sorts of cast changes along the way. We've included enough openings to make it likely that if you had a favorite cast member, he or she will show up somewhere in this video. The theme by Dick DeBenedictis captures well the down-home Southerner about to lead another unsuspecting wrongdoer into his trap. A half-dozen openings plus one dose of the end credits, so you're going to hear a lot of that theme.

title: Matlock - Theme Song (Intro)
description: Matlock ist eine US-amerikanische Krimi- und Justizserie, von der in den Jahren 1986 bis 1995 insgesamt 195 Folgen in insgesamt 9 Staffeln auf 2 US-Sendern entstanden. Die Serie lief von 23. September 1986 bis zum 8. Mai 1992 auf dem US-amerikanischen Fernsehsender NBC; ab dem 5. November 1992 bis zum 7. Mai 1995 wechselte Matlock dann auf den amerikanischen Sender ABC. Als Matlock ab 1986 auf NBC ausgestrahlt wurde, Ã¼bernahm die Serie den bisherigen Sendeplatz des A-Teams. 1997 kehrte Andy Griffith als Ben Matlock noch einmal auf die Bildschirme zurÃ¼ck, diesmal jedoch als Gast einer Doppelfolge in der Serie Diagnose: Mord in der Doppelfolge "Matlock, Retter in der Not" (Originaltitel: Murder Two).

title: Why Julie March Left Matlock for Good
description:
Do you think you know a lot about TV? Try our quiz and enter to win $500!
Click below to check the trivia question

In this video, we're going to discover why Julie Sommars decided to leave Matlock after season 6. Matlock was created by Dean Hargrove and starred Andy Griffith at the show's lead Ben Matlock, a folksy and cantankerous defense attorney that always solves the case. 

Like this content? Subscribe here: 
https://www.youtube.com/factsverse?sub_confirmation=1 

Or, watch more videos here: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLkXAntdjbcSKgHx6EQVOwNKVz1cR2hKVw 

Matlock is a very expensive criminal defense attorney based in Atlanta. He charges $100,000 to take on a case but fortunately, he is worth every last cent. He and fellow lawyers defend his clients by always finding out who the real assailant is. 

His goal is always simply to prove beyond a reasonable doubt his client's innocence and he succeeds almost 100 percent of the time.

title: MATLOCK BATH Derbyshire | Full walking tour of MATLOCK BATH near Matlock, Derbyshire Peak District
description:
Matlock Bath Derbyshire | Walking tour of Matlock Bath near the town of Matlock Derbyshire in the beautiful Peak District
Also watch our tour of Derwent Gardens Matlock Bath ğŸ‘‰ https://youtu.be/4UdbdpNAguo

Matlock Bath is a small village that is said to be the seaside without the beach or sea! It's situated right next door to the town of Matlock Derbyshire England in the Peak District National Park.

We took our cameras for a wander along the 'seafront' type streets of Matlock Bath for a look around and to see what's there! We loved it although there were maybe a few too many fish and chip shops!!

Matlock Bath was the first ever deliberately created tourist attraction village in the UK after thermal spring and spa waters were discovered here. The Victorians absolutely loved spa water and thermal springs and so flocked to this little village in the Derbyshire Dales for breaks and holidays and to relax in the English countryside.

Sometimes (incorrectly) referred to as Matlock Baths, this place offers a lovely day out as you can wander the little shops and pubs as well as take a lovely boat ride along the River Derwent (see our video of Derwent Gardens on our channel!)

There are attractive gardens, wooded hillsides, and limestone crags to explore as well as the main tourist attraction here the Heights Of Abraham Cable Car Ride which takes you right up to the top of the cliffs for some breathtaking views of the beautiful scenery here!

Lord Byron once called Matlock Bath 'Little Switzerland' and the term stuck for a while with tourists and visitors

Another popular tourist attraction is the Matlock Bath Illuminations which happen here annually where the whole riverside is lit up by beautiful coloured lights

Motorcyclists and bikers also come to Matlock Bath in their droves and it really is a sight to see when the bikes come to town and the whole village is packed with Motor bikers and their friends! The whole street gets absolutely soaked in motorbikes and bike culture with the most amazing Motorbikes parked up and down the whole street!

Things to do in Matlock and Matlock Bath; 
As well as the cable car ride that takes you up to The Heights of Abraham and the Victoria Prospect Tower you could also visit The Great Rutland and Masson Caverns which are former lead mines that have been adapted as show caves. 

The Grand Pavilion on South Parade is home to the Peak District Mining Museum. 

For youngsters and families, the nearby theme park of Gulliver's offers hours of fun

There is also an aquarium in Matlock Bath and a photographic museum in the village. 

The Riverside Gardens and Lovers Walks offer a lovely peaceful stroll away from the crowds, and the nearby High Tor affords amazing views from its lofty summit. 

The Derwent Valley Heritage Trail runs through the village of Matlock Bath.

Half a mile south of the Matlock Bath is the shopping centre and working textile museum at Masson Mills. 

I hope you enjoy this walk through the Matlock Peak District area. If so why not subscribe for more videos like this from my channel!

title: MATLOCK Derbyshire | Full walking tour of Matlock Town Centre in the Peak District, England.
description:
Matlock Town is sits in the Derbyshire Peak District of the UK next to Matlock Bath and close to Sheffield, Chesterfield and Derby. This is a walking tour of Matlock Town Centre
Also watch our tour of nearby Matlock Bath ğŸ‘‰ https://youtu.be/lELGZCddQxA

We took the cameras down into the Peak District National Park in the East Midlands and found Matlock Town Centre slap bang right in between Derby and Sheffield. So we thought it would be a good idea to do a full walking tour of Matlock to show you the streets, the buildings and what is happening here.

Matlock is the county town of Derbyshire England. The former spa town of Matlock Bath sits immediately south of the town and is well worth a visit in it's own right due to the tourist attractions there (and to see the sheer number of fish and chip shops!) 

The Shane Meadows movie Dead Mans Shoes was filmed in and around Matlock Town Centre and the wider area in Matlock Dale.

Our Matlock Town walk starts on Dale Road overlooking the River Derwent and we pass underneath the railway bridge that takes the trains in and out of Matlock Train Station.

Walking up Dale Street we pass some noteable places and buildings such as Monk Bar, Riverside Antique Shop, Little Shabby Hen, the old Market Hall and the landmark Olde English Hotel building on the corner of Dale Road and Olde English Road.

Also on the route is W Evans and Son Jewellers Ltd which has been trading in the building with the old clock since 1851 right here in the Matlock Peak District.

Plenty of shops, antique shops and food shops and takeaways line Dale Road which is a busy road as you will see by the volume of traffic going through Matlock Town Centre.

As we reach the end of Dale Road we take a little look up the hill that runs up behind the railway station and then take a right onto Snitterton Road and onto the bridge that sits over the River Derwent.


Our route then takes us along Snitterton Road and round the roundabout onto Bakewell Road before coming round to see Bank Road which used to have a tramway system to take people up and down the road into the town centre!

We then head onto Causeway Lane from where we can see Halls Ley Park. We head along Causeway Lane until we reach the Cafe In The Park at which point we head into Halls Ley Park and down to the victorian Bandstand which is home to many concerts and events held in the park.

Then it's a quick look at the Matlock Flood markers and onto the bridge over to Olde English Car Park and Cool River Cafe and then up to the main high street here in Matlock Town Centre, Dale Road.

I hope you enjoy this walking tour of Matlock Derbyshire. If so why not subscribe now for more videos like this and virtual walks from around the world!

Go behind the scenes as Purl provides rare, candid insight into the difficult decision to leave the show that made her a household name. Purl holds nothing back, speaking openly about the mental health impacts of the demanding filming schedule and the constant pressure to perform.

You'll be moved as she describes the emotional toll of saying goodbye to a character she had poured her heart and soul into for five seasons. A character whose relationship with her brilliant but cantankerous on-screen father, played by the legendary Andy Griffith, had resonated profoundly with fans. Relive nostalgic moments from the show through touching anecdotes and Purl's personal photographs from the set.

Marvel at Purl's courage and self-awareness as she explains prioritizing her mental wellbeing over the prospect of continued fame. Learn how she reinvented herself in the years after, finding fulfillment in passions like music while continuing to act. Drawing inspiration from her life story, reflect on the importance of listening to one's inner voice.

Filled with revelatory insights and profound honesty, this exclusive tell-all takes you behind the curtain to uncover fascinating secrets from one of television's great mysteries. description:
Matlock Episode 6 Recap & Ending Explained: A Painful Retrial Puts Matty Back on Top!
In Matlock Episode 6, the show delivers a riveting courtroom drama centered around a high-stakes retrial. The episode opens with Matty (Matlock) taking on the defense of a wrongfully convicted man, Peter Caldwell, whose case has been reopened after new evidence suggests he may have been framed for murder. The stakes are personal for Matty, as Caldwellâ€™s original trial was handled by a rival attorney, Gerald Stone, who has since built a reputation off the conviction.
This episode is a powerful commentary on the flaws in the justice system and the resilience required to overcome them. Mattyâ€™s ability to uncover the truth, even against a formidable opponent like Stone, cements his place as a top-tier defense attorney. The retrial not only restores Peterâ€™s reputation but also underscores Mattyâ€™s own commitment to justice, putting him "back on top" both legally and morally.

Fans will undoubtedly feel the emotional weight of the episode, which balances courtroom drama with personal stakes, making it one of the standout chapters in the series.

title: PaleyFest LA 2025: Matlock
description:
As part of The Paley Center for Media's 42nd William S. Paley Television Festival, this festival program honors Matlock, the bold reimagining of the classic legal drama. Held at the iconic Dolby Theatre in Hollywood, the panel celebrates the showâ€™s gripping first season, its timely themes, and the creative forces behind its modern revival.

The conversation features cast members Kathy Bates, Jason Ritter, Skye P. Marshall, David Del Rio, and Leah Lewis; along with executive producer/showrunner Jennie Snyder Urman, executive producer/director Kat Coiro, and executive producer Eric Christian Olsen, who also moderates the discussion.

The panel explores the showâ€™s unique origin story, including its unexpected path to production; the influence of the original Matlock series; and why the opioid crisis was made central to the plot. Cast and creators reflect on Kathy Bates' acclaimed performance, character inspirations, and standout scenes from season one. Additional highlights include stories from behind the scenes, personal journeys to the PaleyFest stage, and what fans can expect as the show looks ahead to season two.

title: The BEST Day In MATLOCK BATH, England ğŸ‡¬ğŸ‡§ (Heights of Abraham + MORE!)
description:
Matlock Bath is the perfect day out in the Derbyshire Peak District... according to some people that is!

Welcome to the seaside town with no sea, a place that divides opinion as to whether it's worth visiting or just a massive tourist trap. Join us as we explore the town from a walk down by the River Derwent to its top visitor attraction, The Heights of Abraham! This award winning attraction is not only the top tourist attraction in Matlock Bath, but it's one of the best things to do in the Peak District as a whole.

Ride the cable car to the top of the hill with us before taking tours of 2 different caverns, climbing a tower and exploring the hilltop park. The Heights of Abraham is definitely worth the "must visit" status but it took way longer than we expected which just about left us time to wander the high street which is lined with fish & chip shops, amusements and tut shops.

Best day out in the area or just a massive tourist trap? We'll let you decide!

Matlock, a busy town with so much to do and see in the county of Derbyshire, some of the most popular things to see are the heights of Abraham, Peak District Mining Museum, Critch Tramway Village, Gullivers Kingdom and much much more.
Very popular with the motorbike brigade as a meeting point before or after riding around the dales, through the beautiful Derbyshire countryside.
Matlock was popular during the Victorian era being a spa town and was visited by Princess Victoria before she became queen.

description: Matlock is a popular American television series that originally aired from 1986 to 1995, starring Andy Griffith as Ben Matlock, a sharp, witty, and highly skilled defense attorney from Atlanta. Known for his folksy charm, southern accent, and brilliant courtroom tactics, Matlock takes on complex criminal cases, often defending clients accused of serious crimes. The show mixes drama with light-hearted moments as Matlock meticulously uncovers the truth and exonerates the innocent. Each episode features clever investigations, suspenseful courtroom scenes, and Matlock's unorthodox but effective methods to reveal the true culprit. The series remains beloved for its engaging storytelling, memorable characters, and Andy Griffithâ€™s iconic portrayal of the titular character.

title: Matlock STAR Fired in SHOCK #MeToo Scandal
description:
The CBS series Matlock, the successful legal drama reboot, was thrown into crisis during Season 2 filming when series regular David Del Rio was summarily fired following an allegation of sexual assault by co-star Leah Lewis.
CBS Studios took immediate and unambiguous action on October 2, 2025, concluding an internal investigation and physically removing Del Rio (who played junior associate Billy Martinez) from the set on the same day, signaling a new, zero-tolerance post-#MeToo standard of accountability. This decisive response involved an executive producer overseeing the removal and was meant to mitigate brand damage and project an image of absolute control.
The dismissal created a profound creative crisis: Del Rioâ€™s character, Billy Martinez, was integral to the show's "junior associate trifecta". His firing necessitated the immediate abandonment of a major season-long paternity storyline that had just been established in the Season 2 premiere. The writers' room must now "write out" the character entirely during a six-week planned hiatus, forcing a massive narrative restructuring.
We examine the fallout, including Lewisâ€™s controlled public statement of "strength", the aggressive counter-narrative (and subsequent deletions) from Del Rioâ€™s wife, and how this incident serves as a significant benchmark for crisis management in contemporary television production.

title: MATLOCK BATH | a stunning walk around a lovely Peak District village on a relaxing sunny morning
description:
Welcome, or welcome back, to Wanderlust Walks! Thank you for being here.

Today we are exploring the lovely Peak District village, Matlock Bath. Originally built at the head of a dead-end dirt road running along the valley of the River Derwent from Matlock, the settlement developed in the 19th century as residential and a spa town which remains a tourist destination. In 1698, warm springs were discovered and a bath house was built. As the waters became better known, access was improved by building the bridge into Old Matlock and in 1783, the opening of a new entrance at the south of the valley. We hope you enjoy this scenic walk with us â€” let us know what you think in the comments below!

If you would like to see more videos like this, please give the video a thumbs up and subscribe if you haven't already. If you have any recommendations or suggestions of places for us to visit, let us know in the comments below. With that being said, enjoy! :)

MATLOCK BATH Derbyshire Peak District | Walking Tour | 4K
description:
MATLOCK BATH Derbyshire Peak District | Walking Tour | 4K

Matlock Bath was the first ever deliberately created tourist attraction village in the UK after thermal spring and spa waters were discovered here. 
One of Matlock Bath's standout features is the Heights of Abraham. This 60-acre hilltop park is accessible via mainland Englandâ€™s only Alpine-style cable car. The ride offers panoramic views of the Derwent Valley and leads visitors to attractions like the Victoria Prospect Tower and ancient lead caverns, reflecting the area's mining heritage.
A highlight of the village's calendar is the Matlock Bath Illuminations, an annual event that began in 1897 to celebrate Queen Victoria's Diamond Jubilee. This autumn festival features illuminated boats on the river and a series of light displays,
Matlock Bath is a bikers' paradise. Popular motorcycle routes such as Snake Pass and the UKâ€™s most dangerous road, the Cat and Fiddle, provide great views on the way in and out of the town.

title: Matlock skatepark opening day
description:
Derbyshire Dales District Council's brand new skatepark in Matlock's Hall Leys Park opened to the public on 27 February 2025  - and what a terrific turnout!

Constructed by Fearless Ramps, the new flood resilient stainless-steel structure with composite panels replaces the old wooden skatepark, which had required much maintenance in recent years.

More great news is that our Community Development team is working closely with Hall Leys Skatepark Project to apply for funding towards coaching sessions for beginners and also for an official opening event, which will take place on Saturday 19 July from 11am to 3pm.

It's a massive win for the Skatepark Project group, who started working with us two years ago to identify funding for a new skatepark, only for the Council to successfully apply last year for UK Shared Prosperity Funding from the Government. Match-funding by the Council means the installation cost is now covered.

It's a brilliant example of what a local council can achieve through close working with its community.
